STATUS — OPEN DECISION
----------------------
The final license for this project (open-source vs. proprietary, and which
license) is an OPEN BUSINESS DECISION. See docs/PROJECT-PLAN.md §11 (Open
Questions — monetization / licensing) and docs/ROADMAP.md. Until that decision
is recorded in an Architecture Decision Record under docs/adr/, this repository
is distributed under the following INTERIM terms.

INTERIM TERMS
-------------
All rights reserved. No license, express or implied, is granted to any party to
use, copy, modify, distribute, sublicense, or create derivative works of this
software or its source code, except by separate written agreement with the
copyright holder.

WHY AN INTERIM "ALL RIGHTS RESERVED" NOTICE
-------------------------------------------
Choosing an open-source license is a one-way door: it cannot be revoked for code
already released. An interim "all rights reserved" posture is fully reversible —
the project can be relicensed to any license (a permissive license such as
MIT/Apache-2.0, or a copyleft license) once the monetization model is decided.
Starting permissive-and-public would foreclose options that starting closed
keeps open.

This project deliberately does NOT fork RustDesk (which is AGPL-3.0); it
references the hbbs/hbbr rendezvous+relay topology only as a clean-room
architectural reference. See docs/TECH-STACK.md ("Do NOT fork RustDesk").

